Comment: 0,0:00:04.37,0:00:05.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}英文字幕
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.37,0:00:05.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.03,0:00:10.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Last week we saw Bob and Doug fly to the space station on the Dragon 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.51,0:00:14.97,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}A long-awaited return to flight for US human launch capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.16,0:00:32.38,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And to understand this you have to go back to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.40,0:00:36.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the tragic loss of the Space Shuttle Columbia and her crew in 2003.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.25,0:00:40.67,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At that time a committee of experts were appointed to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.77,0:00:43.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They were named the Columbia Accident Investigation Board.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.09,0:00:50.09,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And for some of them, the more they found out about the Space Shuttle, the less safe it seemed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.36,0:00:55.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Some of them on the accident investigation board actually wanted it grounded permanently.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.05,0:01:01.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}One problem they highlighted was that the retirement date had been set by NASA based upon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.23,0:01:03.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}when they expected a successor to be available.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.76,0:01:10.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In 2001 when the X-33 was canceled, the date of retirement was pushed back from 2012 to 2020.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.33,0:01:17.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The final board reports suggest that the Space Shuttles could be kept flying up until 2010
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.39,0:01:21.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with the prospect of inspection and refurbishment to extend their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.72,0:01:23.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Shuttles were old in years
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.47,0:01:26.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but they were young in terms of the flight time they'd been developed for.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:31.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They had expected weekly or monthly flights back when they were originally designed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.31,0:01:35.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but they couldn't build replacements at least not affordably.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.15,0:01:37.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The last time a Shuttle had been built was Endeavour
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.70,0:01:40.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that was cobbled together over two spare parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.61,0:01:46.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So restarting production would have been about as expensive as developing an entirely new launch vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:52.90,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In 2004, the president announced the way forward with the his Vision for Space Exploration.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.30,0:01:56.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Shuttle was to be set for retirement in 2010
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.47,0:02:01.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}likely based upon the conclusions that the Accident Investigation Board had delivered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.63,0:02:06.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In the same speech he also talks about a new generation of crew exploration vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:09.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}No new development money was immediately available.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.42,0:02:14.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}However there were a number of projects already in development in NASA, which might fit the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.49,0:02:20.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}A year later NASA began something called the Commercial Orbital Transportation Services Program.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.23,0:02:25.59,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it had long been a dream of many to make commercial space services a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.17,0:02:28.28,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA wanted to generate demand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.31,0:02:32.61,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}by asking private companies to deliver cargo to the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.27,0:02:36.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And there was a lot of resistance from people to the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.02,0:02:39.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but the cargo delivery was seen as lower risk than other options.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.75,0:02:44.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Because the world alternatives for cargo delivery from Japan, Europe and Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.09,0:02:46.87,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and that could fill in if things went wrong or were delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.80,0:02:52.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the program was to be managed by the Commercial Crew & Cargo Program Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.41,0:02:55.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Also known as C3PO.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.52,0:02:58.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And with approval of their President and Congress,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.52,0:03:04.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}500 million dollars was set aside to fund initial development of technologies required for commercial services.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.60,0:03:10.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So instead of strict requirements, there were guidelines on what was needed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.09,0:03:15.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}such as the ability to launch 8.4 tons of cargo to the International Space Station every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.90,0:03:22.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with no specification on the number of flights required or any stipulations on how the vehicle should be designed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:28.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Unlike the Space Shuttle, NASA wouldn't own the launch vehicles or the spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.06,0:03:30.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it would simply be buying rides on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.64,0:03:33.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The intellectual property would remain with the developer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.07,0:03:40.03,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Also the program stipulated that the development money awarded had to be matched by private investors
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.40,0:03:44.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to prevent companies being purely reliant on NASA money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.50,0:03:49.52,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The first request for proposals began in January 2006
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.69,0:03:54.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and twenty-one proposals were delivered before the March sixth deadline
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:04:00.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and these came from a range of companies including existing NASA suppliers like Lockheed, Boeing,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.40,0:04:04.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}through the new space startups that we knew today such as SpaceX
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.37,0:04:10.29,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and at least according to one account, somebody who was going to build a rocket engine in their garage.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.73,0:04:14.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}After the selection process, the two finalists chosen were
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.05,0:04:19.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX who had pitched a larger version of their Falcon 1 rocket, the Falcon 9
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.28,0:04:25.63,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and Rocketplane Kistler with their K1 reused rocket running on high-performance Russian engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.14,0:04:31.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At this point SpaceX had tried one launch of its Falcon 1 rocket which had failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.68,0:04:36.12,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And in 2006 was the year then that the Constellation Program got her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.41,0:04:39.33,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Bits of it had been in development since 2001
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:41.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but this brought them all together under one roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:47.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was an ambitious program using Shuttle-derived hardware for the Ares 1 and Ares 5 rockets
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.04,0:04:52.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which would launch a new crew exploration vehicle, which we now know as Orion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:59.60,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Crew Exploration Vehicle had been conceived in the 1990s with official planning beginning in 2004
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.83,0:05:03.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the contract being awarded to Lockheed in 2006.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.73,0:05:06.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And as you know, it's still not really ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:11.69,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Anyway, the Constellation Program was pitched as being the replacement for the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.01,0:05:14.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the program that would take astronauts back to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.34,0:05:20.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Ares 1 would use a single solid say a five segment rocket booster
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.42,0:05:23.55,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}derived from the Shuttle design which only has four segments.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.86,0:05:30.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It would have an upper stage that was powered by a J-2X engine develop a burning hydrogen and oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:37.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Ares 5 on the other hand was a monster heavy lift vehicle a bit like the SLS
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:41.79,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but bigger and able to put 188 tons into low-earth orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.58,0:05:46.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In 2007 the agreement with Kistler was then terminated
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.80,0:05:51.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}because they had been unable to raise the private funds needed to match the NASA money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:54.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And another rental proposals were were made.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:59.94,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}NASA chose instead Orbital Sciences Corporation with their Cygnus cargo vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.12,0:06:03.77,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the Taurus 2 rocket which is now known as the Antares.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:06.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Meanwhile SpaceX was in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.94,0:06:09.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The Falcon 1 rocket launchers were failing to reach orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.78,0:06:12.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The first three flights were all failures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:18.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and Elon Musk often mentions how SpaceX would have shut down if the fourth flight had not succeeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.70,0:06:24.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And you'll be unsurprised to hear that in 2008 they succeeded their first launch of a Falcon 1 rocket
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.66,0:06:30.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}paving the way for their one only commercial launch of the Falcon 1 in 2009.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.56,0:06:37.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2009 would also see a new president and one of the first space policy decisions he made
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.67,0:06:41.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}was to create a committee to study the current state of affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.36,0:06:46.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Officially known as the review of United States human space flight plans committee.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.33,0:06:52.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Better known as the Augustine Commission after the chairman Norman Augustine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.36,0:06:55.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}He actually chaired a similar Commission 20 years earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.07,0:06:57.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and so he had a lot of respect at doing this kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.31,0:07:01.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So the Commission did their work
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.55,0:07:24.46,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And at the current funding levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.57,0:07:27.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}they estimated it would be as late as 2020
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.79,0:07:32.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}before it was able to launch a single crew to the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.69,0:07:36.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And so in response to this space policy changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.34,0:07:40.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The president drove a stronger commitment to commercial space services.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.37,0:07:43.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Not only approving the Commercial Resupply Services Program
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.45,0:07:47.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that paid SpaceX and Orbital Sciences for delivering cargo to the ISS,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.88,0:07:52.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but in 2010, the Commercial Crew Development Program started.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.72,0:07:53.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It was expected that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.84,0:08:00.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Commercial Crew providers would be able to develop the capability and deliver to the ISS as early as 2015.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.05,0:08:07.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Constellation was essentially defunded and many politicians in Congress were unhappy that with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.00,0:08:14.17,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Partly because they didn't really have control over the allocation of contracts to the commercial programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:18.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So this really represented a loss of control and a loss of money to their states.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.24,0:08:22.51,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In the end the parts of Constellation that had been developed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.63,0:08:28.08,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}including the Orion spacecraft and the five segment boosters and the RL-10 engines upgrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.49,0:08:30.80,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Those all became part of the SLS program.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.15,0:08:36.39,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Meanwhile huge parts of Constellation weren't useful. Much of it was still on the drawing board
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.41,0:08:40.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and the singular launch that they made was the Ares 1x
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.10,0:08:43.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which took a regular four segment Shuttle booster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:46.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It added an extension to make it look like a five segment booster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.07,0:08:49.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They added a boilerplate upper stage
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.46,0:08:52.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and even that single launch with half the equipment
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.97,0:08:57.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}was almost as expensive as the entire Commercial Crew Development Program.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:09:00.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}To that point it was about four hundred million dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.54,0:09:04.58,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SLS was less capable than the Ares 5
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.60,0:09:08.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but it was much more likely to deliver on a reasonable timescale.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.36,0:09:15.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Also the Ares 1 was considered to be much more dangerous than any other human launch options proposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.71,0:09:18.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There was a great paper on how dangerous this would have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.40,0:09:23.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In 2010 also saw the first flight of SpaceX's Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In fact it's 10 years ago tomorrow on Thursday
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.17,0:09:34.02,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that the first Falcon 9 launched carrying a boilerplate upper stage simulation of the Dragon capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.40,0:09:38.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The 1.0 version of Falcon 9 is quite different from what we know today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.88,0:09:42.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The nine engines are arranged in a grid instead of an Octaweb.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.94,0:09:44.57,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The stages are shorter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.59,0:09:47.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and of course there's no landing legs or grid fins.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:53.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX did however include parachutes to test recovery they didn't get any success with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.94,0:09:58.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And in all of this, the most important decision was the commitment to Commercial Crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.90,0:10:01.45,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Commercial Cargo hadn't even been demonstrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.45,0:10:07.37,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So to committing to privately funded crew launches requires a lot of faith in private industry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.45,0:10:09.92,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}being able to deliver something completely new
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.92,0:10:13.68,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}in a timeline faster than the existing government development process.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.32,0:10:17.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}So 2011 will that saw the last flight of the Space Shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:22.71,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It actually been extended by one year to allow completion of the International Space Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.38,0:10:30.11,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2011 also saw SpaceX is first award from NASA to develop a crew capable version of their dragon cargo capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.94,0:10:34.22,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In May of 2012 SpaceX became the first private company
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.24,0:10:40.84,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to successfully dock spacecraft to the International Space Station in Dragon Demo Flight 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.86,0:10:46.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And later that year they began their semi regular Commercial Resupply Services missions to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.50,0:10:54.39,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2013 brought us the Falcon 9 1.1 with the extended tanks and the silhouette that we today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.68,0:10:58.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And also the first attempts at using rocket engines to land the boosters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:01.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In the early years of the Commercial Crew Program,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.36,0:11:06.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}there were also ongoing efforts to overturn those presidential funding requests.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.37,0:11:08.25,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Every few months there'll be hearings
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.41,0:11:13.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with the NASA Administrator going to Congress to ask for the program to be properly funded.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.41,0:11:15.75,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This would of course be delayed development.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.78,0:11:19.49,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The proposals they had expected you know launches as early as 2015
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:23.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but the continual underfunding made those untenable.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.54,0:11:27.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And of course such rosy timelines didn't factor into the extra development time needed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.80,0:11:30.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}to deal with the problems with the parachutes for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.32,0:11:37.74,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2014 also saw the actual contracts being awarded for Commercial Crew Services with two finalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.08,0:11:44.85,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Boeing could expect to receive up to 4.2 billion while SpaceX's contract could earn it 2.6 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:46.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now this isn't money that was paid out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.56,0:11:51.16,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This is the flights so far have all been funded through the development program.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.10,0:11:56.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2015 had the first actual test flight on the Commercial Crew Program
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.46,0:12:00.62,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}with SpaceX demonstrating the Dragon to pad abort capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.92,0:12:03.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}However in June the CRS 7 mission failed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.79,0:12:08.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}due to the second stage oxygen tank rupturing after a helium cylinder broke phillipe free
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:13.78,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Falcon 9 would be grounded during the investigation and it returned to flight in December.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.92,0:12:16.36,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This was a new variant called The Full thrust.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:22.01,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This used a deep chilled densified propellant to get more performance from the same size of fuel tanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.59,0:12:27.64,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}This mission would also be the first to successfully land and recover the first stage booster at the launch site.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.06,0:12:31.65,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And this booster is the one that's on display at SpaceX headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.16,0:12:37.20,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}By 2016 most of the funding fights over Commercial Crew were over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.59,0:12:40.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There did continue to be a steady stream of diehards
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.37,0:12:44.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}looking for any excuse to redirect Commercial Crew funds elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.56,0:12:47.24,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}SpaceX continued developing as booster recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.27,0:12:51.31,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}They landed several boosters over the year on land and on their drone ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.54,0:12:56.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}However in september, SpaceX suffered another dramatic failure on the pad
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.67,0:12:59.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}when they were loading propellants to test-fire the engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.77,0:13:03.34,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}There would be no more flights for the year while it was being investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:07.41,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In 2017 there was a new president in the White House
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.45,0:13:12.98,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}but NASA funding for commercial space operations remained essentially untouched by the new administration.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.56,0:13:18.53,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Falcon 9 returned to flight and in March it performed the first re-flight of a booster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.78,0:13:23.66,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2017 also saw the debut of the Block 4 booster design with its upgraded engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.16,0:13:27.00,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2018 debuted the Falcon Heavy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.08,0:13:32.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and while many of you remember the red roadster carrying Starman off on the cruise into deep space,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.20,0:13:35.96,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}it wasn't hugely relevant to the Commercial Crew Program.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.25,0:13:41.21,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But later in that year the introduction of the Block 5 version of a Falcon 9 was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:46.13,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Now Block 5 was supposed to represent the final evolution of the Block Falcon 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.37,0:13:49.81,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Any stable state that could be approved to fly crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.32,0:13:51.89,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}In August of 2018,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.05,0:13:55.72,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the astronauts who would fly the first missions and commercial crew were announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.88,0:14:00.56,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}Of course at that point they were still expecting the astronauts would fly in 2019.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:05.40,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}And 2019 did see the first flight of a Crew Dragon in March.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.74,0:14:10.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}It launched safely and traveled to the space station carrying Ripley, the test dummy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.33,0:14:13.19,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and Plushy Earth and some extra cargo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.67,0:14:15.10,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The capsule returned to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.14,0:14:19.86,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and was expected to be recovered and refurbished and used for an in-flight abort test.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.94,0:14:24.99,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}But in April a ground test destroyed the capsule in a fiery explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.34,0:14:27.07,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The investigation would take months
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.07,0:14:31.30,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and ultimately require a redesign of the propellant system for their abort thrusters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.88,0:14:37.06,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}At the end of 2019 Boeing also performed a test flight of their Starliner spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.07,0:14:39.04,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and while the launch was perfect,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.45,0:14:44.88,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}the capsule had many problems once in space, largely blamed on poorly tested software.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.14,0:14:48.18,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}The capsule never made his planned rendezvous with the station
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.41,0:14:50.76,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}and there were enough questions raised about the flight
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:54.15,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}that Boeing is planning a second test flight later this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:14:57.73,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}2019 also saw the launch of the Artemis program
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.76,0:15:01.42,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}which is expected to use a lot more Commercial Crew capabilities
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:07.82,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}or commercial launch capabilities than the original backers of the SLS predicted in 2010.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.96,0:15:32.44,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}bringing to an end the gap in spaceflight that resulted from decisions made almost twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.00,0:15:35.32,1080P-src-hans-sans-Bold-50,,0,0,0,,{\blur4}I'm Scott Manley. Fly safe.
